<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23D5789FF93E538D55AFD02D6854684" box="[826,911,723,744]" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is found in shallow (about 10–40-cm deep), temporary channels within dense rainforest, in teacoloured and acidic (pH 3.5–4.0) water that contains litter at the bottom. No other fishes were found at this habitat, but some temporary channels may be in contact with small creeks containing the rivulid 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D55AFC5BD1A947CC" authority="Kohler, 1906" authorityName="Kohler" authorityYear="1906" box="[826,1187,906,928]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="santensis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D55AFC5BD10F47CC" box="[826,1029,906,928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Rivulus santensis</emphasis>
Köhler, 1906
</taxonomicName>
, the characids 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D335FC5AD1BC47D3" authority="(Nichols, 1913)" baseAuthorityName="Nichols" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Mimagoniates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D335FC5AD6F447D2" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Mimagoniates lateralis</emphasis>
(Nichols, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D2A3FC78D10947B1" authority="Myers, 1926" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1926" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Rachoviscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassiceps">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D2A3FC78D66347B1" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Rachoviscus crassiceps</emphasis>
Myers, 1926
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D226FC16D1904790" authority="(Eigenmann &amp; Norris, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Eigenmann &amp; Norris" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Hollandichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D226FC16D0AB47B0" box="[1094,1441,967,988]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hollandichthys multifasciatus</emphasis>
(Eigenmann &amp; Norris, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
, and the callichthyid 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D55AFBD4D01B4077" authority="(Regan, 1913)" baseAuthorityName="Regan" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[826,1297,1029,1051]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Callichthyidae" genus="Scleromystax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropterus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D55AFBD4D16C4076" box="[826,1126,1029,1050]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Scleromystax macropterus</emphasis>
(Regan, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
. The area is undergoing slight urbanization, making 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D376FBF5D652403B" authority="Costa, 2008" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="itanhaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D376FBF5D652403B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">L. itanhaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23D5789FF93E538D53FFB93D6BE403B" box="[863,948,1090,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
an endangered species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF93E538D55AFB50D68D409F" blockId="7.[826,1441,1153,1267]" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D55AFB50D6B240FA" box="[826,952,1153,1174]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF93E538D220FB50D1C940FA" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" box="[1088,1219,1153,1174]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="itanhaensis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF93E538D220FB50D1C940FA" box="[1088,1219,1153,1174]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">itanhaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
denotes the occurrence of the new species in the Itanhaém river basin, an isolated small coastal drainage of south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7670FF93E538D55AFB0CD689409F" box="[826,899,1245,1267]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
